# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Market Research → Meta Ads — environment config
#  Copy this file to ".env" and fill in the key(s) for the providers you use.
#  Keys stay on the backend and are NEVER sent to the browser. .env is git-ignored.
#
#  You can also set providers/keys per stage in the app's ⚙ LLMs panel instead
#  of here — handy for trying a different model without editing files.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Defaults: Perplexity for research, Claude for writing ───────────────────
# These are the recommended defaults. Set the keys for the providers you'll use;
# you don't need all of them.

# Research stage. Perplexity does live web retrieval (mining real reviews/forums),
# which a plain LLM can't. Get a key: https://www.perplexity.ai/settings/api
# A deep-research run is usually a few cents to ~$0.30 and takes 1–3 minutes.
PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=

# Writing stage (segments, angles, headlines). Get a key: https://console.anthropic.com/
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ── Other providers (optional) — set a key to use it from the ⚙ LLMs panel ──
# Any of these can drive either stage. OpenRouter alone reaches almost every
# model (GPT, Claude, Gemini, Llama, …); use an `:online` model there for research.
OPENAI_API_KEY=
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# Custom / self-hosted OpenAI-compatible endpoint (Ollama, LM Studio, vLLM, a
# private gateway, …). Set the key (use any non-empty value if none is required)
# and the base URL.
CUSTOM_API_KEY=
# CUSTOM_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1

# ── Change the default provider/model per stage (optional) ──────────────────
# Provider ids: perplexity | anthropic | openai | openrouter | custom
# RESEARCH_PROVIDER=perplexity
# RESEARCH_MODEL=sonar-deep-research
# WRITING_PROVIDER=anthropic
# WRITING_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6

# ── Server ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Port the backend API listens on. Only change if 8787 is taken.
# PORT=8787

# ── Curated "Official" templates (shared with everyone) ──────────────────────
# Raw URL of a curated-templates.json the app fetches on load, so the owner's
# winning ad templates reach every install automatically. Leave blank to use
# only the copy bundled in the app. Set this to your repo's raw file once pushed,
# e.g. https://raw.githubusercontent.com/<you>/<repo>/main/curated-templates.json
# VITE_CURATED_TEMPLATES_URL=
